			<ns0:name>shcherb...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/105197577636354702799/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">There are number instructions variants that explicitly introduce data16 prefix (example: 'ja Jw, data16 0x0f 0x87, branch_hint nacl-forbidden'). In such cases rexw bit is expected to be zero. Technically, processor allows to combine rexw=1 and data16, but in such cases rexw=1 takes precedence, so it would mean instruction with different operand size.

Perhaps, 'norexw' attribute should be explicitly added to all such instructions.

